name: 欧文·帕特里克·乔伊纳
name_full: 欧文·帕特里克·乔伊纳 Owen Patrick Joyner

last_movies.title: 高中前要做的一百件事 第一季

introduction: Owen Patrick Joyner is best known for his role as Alex in Netflix hit series "Julie and the Phantoms", a Kenny Ortega production. Owen Patrick Joyner was born July 19, 2000 in Oklahoma. Owen began acting on stage at a young age and landed his first television project: Nickelodeon's "100 Things To Do Before High School" as Christian 'Crispo' Powers. "100 Things To Do Before High School" was created and produced by Scott Fellows. Owen has appeared in hit shows like the "Thundermans", "It's On" (pilot). "Nickelodeon's Ho Ho Holiday" and the feature film "The Veil" directed by Jeff Goldberg. Owen's project preceding "Julie and the phantoms" was Nickelodeon's "Knight Squad" were Owen plays the lead role of Arc, the head of his four-member team navigating their way through Knight School. "Knight Squad" was created by Sean William Cunningham, Marc Dworkin and directed by Trevor Kirschner.
